column5: First half pure bliss, second half pure pain. Body was not wanting it today. Rather, body merely expressed the conditioning it was in given the stimulus and it was not as my mind expected or desired. Slowed down the pace and let go of expecting a particular finishing time. Enjoying the terrain and scenery which were both continually inspiring. Proud to find gratitude in the pain and push through to the end, hobbling down the mountain. Thankful brothers were there waiting for me. A unique experience I will remember fondly!
